sentence: Among the underlying components of the S&P 500 index, we saw noteworthy options trading volume today in Procter & Gamble Company (Symbol: PG), where a total of 33,663 contracts have traded so far, representing approximately 3.4 million underlying shares.
That amounts to about 51.8% of PG's average daily trading volume over the past month of 6.5 million shares.

Particularly high volume was seen for the $97.50 strike call option expiring February 16, 2018 , with 25,429 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 2.5 million underlying shares of PG.

Below is a chart showing PG's trailing twelve month trading history, with the $97.50 strike highlighted in orange:

Oracle Corp (Symbol: ORCL) saw options trading volume of 50,862 contracts, representing approximately 5.1 million underlying shares or approximately 42.7% of ORCL's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 11.9 million shares.

Especially high volume was seen for the $51 strike call option expiring December 15, 2017 , with 15,174 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 1.5 million underlying shares of ORCL.

Below is a chart showing ORCL's trailing twelve month trading history, with the $51 strike highlighted in orange:

And Adobe Systems Inc (Symbol: ADBE) options are showing a volume of 9,171 contracts thus far today.
That number of contracts represents approximately 917,100 underlying shares, working out to a sizeable 41.8% of ADBE's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 2.2 million shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $195 strike call option expiring January 19, 2018 , with 1,175 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 117,500 underlying shares of ADBE.

Below is a chart showing ADBE's trailing twelve month trading history, with the $195 strike highlighted in orange:
